<dl id="n30160g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30160g">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30160g"> 160(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font>a postillione</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Sentries thoroughly fatigued have fallen asleep on their feet and remained standing. <mark>Postillions</mark>, in the good old coaching days, often fell asleep on horseback and yet rode on in the saddle. <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 22</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
